JOHANNESBURG - There is some good news for consumers heading into the festive season as the Automobile Association is predicting a slight fuel price drop in the first week of November. WATCH:  Are SA pay cheques getting smaller? A decrease of between eight and 18 cents a litre is expected, depending on the grade. The Automobile Association's Layton Beard explained the drop is mostly due to a plateau of the global oil price. READ: October's fuel price up and down In October, the price of 95 octane petrol increased by 18 cents a litre while the price of 93 octane dropped by 4 cents a litre. Diesel and wholesale Illuminating paraffin increased by 25 cents a litre.